WEBVTT

00:03.970 --> 00:07.553
I'm wrapping up the series of kingdom powers.

00:08.174 --> 00:10.676
And this one is part eight.

00:11.017 --> 00:13.259
Amen, we've been in this series for two months.

00:14.100 --> 00:16.402
And it's been kind of a growing series.

00:17.182 --> 00:25.951
We need to grow up in Christ and we need to learn to align ourselves with God's values.

00:26.571 --> 00:27.492
Do you believe that today?

00:27.512 --> 00:29.854
Align yourself with God's values.

00:29.974 --> 00:33.778
And we discovered

00:34.210 --> 00:39.357
through the series that humility is greater than pride.

00:40.278 --> 00:40.919
We know that.

00:41.479 --> 00:46.025
And so we know that sometimes pride will try to get a hold of us at times.

00:46.646 --> 00:49.169
But don't ever get too big for your britches.

00:49.750 --> 00:50.551
Amen.

00:50.971 --> 00:52.994
Don't ever get too big for your britches.

00:53.074 --> 00:53.415
Amen.

00:53.995 --> 00:58.461
And the Bible says, if you think you know something, you don't know anything yet.

00:59.082 --> 00:59.943
Amen.

00:59.963 --> 01:02.386
In other words, you might think you know something

01:02.498 --> 01:04.400
But you don't know anything yet.

01:05.101 --> 01:07.123
The Bible says we only see in part.

01:07.924 --> 01:12.269
And we will see fully when we have our glorified bodies.

01:12.349 --> 01:14.731
But that's why it's called faith.

01:15.112 --> 01:16.413
Don't you wish you knew it all?

01:17.414 --> 01:17.535
Amen.

01:17.555 --> 01:20.538
It would be nice to know it all, know what's gonna go down the pike.

01:20.978 --> 01:24.743
But that's where we gotta get up and step out in faith.

01:24.863 --> 01:26.384
Amen.

01:26.504 --> 01:29.728
It's sometimes our walk with Christ is a mystery.

01:30.148 --> 01:31.570
Have you ever noticed that?

01:31.650 --> 01:32.591
And I love that.

01:32.651 --> 01:37.177
So it says here in James 4-6, but he gives more grace.

01:38.239 --> 01:44.106
Therefore, he says, God resists the proud, but gives grace to the humble.

01:44.627 --> 01:48.472
So if you're walking in pride, God's going to actively resist you.

01:48.492 --> 01:50.134
Amen.

01:50.234 --> 01:52.237
I don't hear any amens here, amen.

01:52.637 --> 01:56.402
But if you're walking in grace, God's going to actively embrace you.

01:57.250 --> 01:58.632
I like that, amen?

01:58.972 --> 02:03.779
We found out in the second week that generosity is greater than greed.

02:04.440 --> 02:08.805
And sometimes we want to hold on to what we have, but God is saying, let go.

02:08.846 --> 02:11.609
And we need to learn to let go, amen?

02:12.010 --> 02:21.362
As it says in 2 Corinthians 9, as is written, he has dispersed abroad, he has given to the poor, his righteousness endures forever.

02:21.402 --> 02:24.146
So amen, somebody say, I'm a giver.

02:24.962 --> 02:28.146
Amen and that's a part of God's nature.

02:28.927 --> 02:35.956
God is a giver and we are givers and we found out in the third week that faith is greater than fear.

02:35.996 --> 02:39.401
Has anybody ever dealt with any fear in here?

02:39.461 --> 02:46.610
Has anybody ever had any kind of trial in your life and the devil is trying to make you nervous?

02:47.042 --> 03:02.847
and the devil will try to make us nervous at times, but I'm gonna say that if you are in God and that boat might be reeling and rocking, maybe the storm is coming out, but if Jesus is in your boat, you can't go down.

03:03.688 --> 03:04.670
You believe that today?

03:04.730 --> 03:15.026
And so this is a great scripture here, pertain to faith is greater than fear, for we walk by faith and not by sight.

03:15.810 --> 03:18.353
Somebody say, I'm not looking at circumstances.

03:19.454 --> 03:22.477
So we can't be focused on the circumstances.

03:22.537 --> 03:24.419
We gotta be focused on Jesus.

03:25.280 --> 03:30.826
You focus on Jesus, you will make it to the other side every time.

03:30.846 --> 03:31.347
You believe that?

03:31.807 --> 03:35.771
Then we found out healing is greater than sickness.

03:36.072 --> 03:37.253
How many people believe that?

03:38.134 --> 03:41.938
And you know, there was no sickness that Jesus could not cure.

03:42.658 --> 03:49.388
Have you ever read the Bible and read all the accounts that Jesus healed all these people, delivered all these people?

03:49.829 --> 03:52.132
And there wasn't one that stopped Jesus.

03:52.633 --> 03:52.974
Amen.

03:53.414 --> 03:54.236
He was able.

03:54.316 --> 03:59.644
So healing is always wins over sickness.

04:00.185 --> 04:11.442
And in Matthew 8, 17 says that it might be fulfilled, which was spoken by Isaiah, the prophet saying, he himself took our infirmities and he bore our sicknesses.

04:11.938 --> 04:17.467
And then another week we talked about rest is greater than stress.

04:18.208 --> 04:23.377
And I'm telling you the devil is trying to get some of us stressed out in here, but I'm not going to get stressed out.

04:24.298 --> 04:27.323
I'm going to learn to cast my cares on the Lord.

04:27.383 --> 04:30.688
I'm not going to take the care upon me.

04:30.728 --> 04:32.051
That's what prayer is all about.

04:32.551 --> 04:32.892
Amen.

04:32.972 --> 04:37.940
Prayer is taking it to the Lord, giving it to him and walking away.

04:38.261 --> 04:39.122
Glory to God.

04:39.426 --> 04:48.721
And I like what it says in Matthew 11, 28, come to me, all you are labor and heavy laden and I will give you rest.

04:49.282 --> 04:52.326
The bottom line is we just got to yoke up with Jesus.

04:52.927 --> 04:58.296
His yoke is easy and his burdens are heavy.

04:58.316 --> 05:00.620
No, his burdens are light.

05:00.680 --> 05:02.042
It's easy in Jesus.

05:02.603 --> 05:07.250
When you're doing it in Jesus is easy, but when you're trying to do it in your own power,

05:07.746 --> 05:09.208
Somebody say God power.

05:10.229 --> 05:11.930
See, I gotta do it in God's power.

05:12.010 --> 05:14.012
I can't do it in my own power, amen?

05:14.453 --> 05:18.777
Will power will only go so far, but God's power will take you to the other side.

05:19.358 --> 05:20.199
Do you believe that today?

05:20.579 --> 05:23.462
Then we talked about wisdom is greater than foolishness.

05:23.502 --> 05:25.464
Anybody ever done any foolish things in here?

05:26.285 --> 05:27.226
Glory to God.

05:28.427 --> 05:29.969
Yeah, I left the church for a little while.

05:30.009 --> 05:30.890
That was foolish.

05:31.350 --> 05:34.994
And when I left the church, this was many years ago before I was a pastor, amen?

05:35.074 --> 05:39.881
